      "specificArticles": [
        {
          "textContent": "Here is one of the biggest open pit from Europe. How does it looks like and what are the consequences? Let's hit the road... From the Historic Center we head to the the 'Tăul Mare' Lake and then to the Copper Open Pit - Rosia Poieni. Here is a dessert landscape: dry soil, no vegetables, a shaved mountain and rusty huge machines. Next you will pass by some traditional villages with an authentic charm: Muntari, Poiana and Vința. Once you will see a big lake with powerful colors of red and blue, you reached the waste lake Geamana. Next, an unpaved road will lead you by the Geamana dam to the Lupșa Monastery where you will also find a good <b>restaurant</b>. Return to Casa Petri, through Bistra and Carpenis villages on an asphalted road. The road from Cooper Open Pit to Geamana is quite long, so you can get back at Casa Petri and go to 'Geamana' by car on asphalted road.",
